            <SimpleData name="Data_Manager">UNAVCO (for raw GPS data and Rinex); AOOS/Axiom for convereted water level</SimpleData>
            <SimpleData name="Variable_Names">sea_surface_height_above_sea_level</SimpleData>
            <SimpleData name="Additional_notes">AOOS contracted with JOA Surveys to prepare portable code for Axiom to use to convert the GNSS data to water level.  We are comparing converted data water quality between the Orion sourced code Axiom is using and what JOA has developed for processing GNSS-R data. At some point, we will stop supporting one of the St. Michaels data feeds.  Water level data currently on the portal are releative to the GPS antenna. We need to adjust the data to a MLLW / Datum  and resolve  many drop outs in the datastream (probably due to satellite signal issues, but some due to plotting algorithm). Water level currently plotted with respect to the antenna height. </SimpleData>
            <SimpleData name="file">AOOS.xlsx</SimpleData>
          </SchemaData>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -162.006498,63.483962,0
