            <SimpleData name="Variable_Names">sea_water_temperature, sea_surface_wave_mean_period, sea_surface_wave_directional_spread,  sea_surface_wave_period_at_variance_spectral_density_maximum, sea_surface_wave_significant_height, sea_surface_wave_from_direction, wind_speed, wind_from_direction</SimpleData>
            <SimpleData name="Additional_notes">These are seasonally deployed wave buoys as part of a University of Alaska, Alaska Coastal Cooperative project with NSF (ACTION). AOOS and Tetra Tech (Formerly Axiom Data Science) are partners on this project for data management. Deployments also occurred in 2024, but these data were not uploaded to the AOOS Data Portal until 2025. Future deployments will likely be called out as separate stations, due to locational differences from year to year. These station deployments likely will need to updated and changed annually. This buoy broke from its mooring in November and became a drifter. Data for the drifter component of this deployment is currently being added to the AOOS Data Portal and will be added to 2026 ASSET INVENTORY.  list of all UAF ACC deployments here: https://portal.aoos.org/#metadata/2398/sensor_source</SimpleData>
